data.text: @AskAkbar Isn't commonwealth a legacy of British empire's colonial past?

Their first rendezvous together was in Prince Harry's "adopted home" in Botswana. Their embrace of the Commonwealth reflects their universal and inclusive worldview and symbolizes the new 21st century view of one world.

It is worth noting too that both Harry and Meghan are strongly committed to the Commonwealth. Prince Harry is a Commonwealth Youth Ambassador, and Meghan's bridal veil featured flowers from each of the 53 Commonwealth countries.

The city center was full of hundreds packed together watching the wedding on TV, with lots of music, singing, and clapping. I send my warmest congrats to the newlyweds, to all their relatives, and to the nations they represent.
All of Britain is in love with the happy couple and is celebrating - even the weather was beautiful today, with lots of sun. I’m in Cambridge this weekend and there is a festival-like atmosphere.

The marriage reinforces the special relationship between the US and UK, which in this turbulent world remains most important. Meghan Markle herself is a tremendous bridge between cultures and races. She is like a fresh breeze and adds vitality and beauty to the House of Windsor.
